        "content": "<ol>\n<li>What is the current state of topological vector spaces and distribution theory in mathlib? Maybe I'm getting confused by the generality, but I could not find any notion of a TVS or a definition of the space of distributions (on some open set) for example.</li>\n<li>Is anyone working on this? If so, how can I contribute?</li>\n</ol>",
        "id": 417266035,
        "sender_full_name": "Michiel Huttener",
        "timestamp": 1705940283
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Right now we have <em>unbundled</em> topological vector spaces, which you would write like this:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kd\">variable</span> <span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"bp\">ùïú</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span> <span class=\"o\">:</span> <span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">NormedField</span> <span class=\"bp\">ùïú</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">AddCommGroup</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">Module</span> <span class=\"bp\">ùïú</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">TopologicalSpace</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n  <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">TopologicalAddGroup</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span> <span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">ContinuousSMul</span> <span class=\"bp\">ùïú</span> <span class=\"n\">V</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>(Of course, the <code>NormedField ùïú</code> condition could be relaxed.)</p>",
        "id": 417267175,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1705940606
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"311453\">@Fr√©d√©ric Dupuis</span> or <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"214703\">@Yury G. Kudryashov</span> might be the correct people to ask about the status of this in Mathlib.</p>",
        "id": 417267393,
        "sender_full_name": "Jireh Loreaux",
        "timestamp": 1705940662
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>There are several notions called \"distribution\". Which one are you talking about?</p>",
        "id": 417267590,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1705940726
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>As for TVS, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"197836\">@Jireh Loreaux</span> is right; <code>[Module k V] [ContinuousSMul k V]</code> is the way we write it at the moment.</p>",
        "id": 417267869,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1705940809
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Also, sometimes <code>[Module k V] [ContinuousConstSMul k V]</code> is enough.</p>",
        "id": 417267921,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1705940824
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I seem to recall <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"268315\">@Anatole Dedecker</span> working on something like this.</p>",
        "id": 417268373,
        "sender_full_name": "Fr√©d√©ric Dupuis",
        "timestamp": 1705940953
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Distribution_(mathematics)\">Distributions in the sense of Schwartz</a></p>",
        "id": 417268708,
        "sender_full_name": "Michiel Huttener",
        "timestamp": 1705941053
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SchwartzMap#doc\">docs#SchwartzMap</a>, looking for the dual space.</p>",
        "id": 417269330,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1705941218
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Probably, <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"412682\">@Moritz Doll</span> uses continuous linear maps from <code>SchwartzMap</code> instead of introducing a new definition.</p>",
        "id": 417269742,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1705941313
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Thanks for the responses! I'll start by playing around with the type classes. <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f642\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 417271180,
        "sender_full_name": "Michiel Huttener",
        "timestamp": 1705941739
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>'normal' distributions are the dual of compactly smooth functions, the dual of <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib4_docs/find/?pattern=SchwartzMap#doc\">docs#SchwartzMap</a> is usually called the space of tempered distributions.</p>",
        "id": 417325472,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz Doll",
        "timestamp": 1705961730
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Anatole wrote a lot of stuff for <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msubsup><mi>C</mi><mi>c</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">‚àû</mi></msubsup></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">C_c^\\infty</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.9303em;vertical-align:-0.247em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">C</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.453em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">c</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">‚àû</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">‚Äã</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.247em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>, but I don't know whether it is PR'd</p>",
        "id": 417325759,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz Doll",
        "timestamp": 1705961861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>for tempered distributions you can see from the file that defining things like the dirac delta is not too hard. We are missing a useful criterion to talk about convergence of distributions (the topology is defined, but very abstractly)</p>",
        "id": 417326010,
        "sender_full_name": "Moritz Doll",
        "timestamp": 1705961971
    },
    {
